{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"wormy-grail-cherry","description":"# Correct completion-gate child-closure docs (superseded by 30c2ef3ad)\n\n## What\nCommit `30c2ef3ad` split \"uncertified child\" from \"blocking child\": only an UNCLOSED direct child\nis now a deterministic FAIL; a closed-but-uncertified (force-closed) child lets the parent close\nUNSIGNED with `certifiable=false` (the LLM still runs on the parent's own criteria). The docs still\ndescribe the old semantics.\n\nFiles/lines to correct:\n- `docs/llm-framework.md:381-395` — \"any child not closed+certified -> FAIL without the LLM\" /\n  \"LLM only reached once all children are closed+signed\" (both now false); document `certifiable`.\n- `docs/llm-framework.md:424-427`, `docs/workflow-engine.md:35-37`, `CLAUDE.md` completion-gate\n  section — the \"unsigned close ⇒ validation did not pass\" biconditional (now has 2-3 causes).\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/completion-verification.yaml:5-6` — description contradicts its own ops.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `llm-framework.md` child-closure section rewritten around blocking vs certification-withholding;\n      the `certifiable` verdict field documented.\n- [ ] The \"unsigned close\" claim qualified in all three docs (PASS signs iff certifiable).\n- [ ] The gate YAML description corrected; commit carries a `rebar-ticket:` trailer.","id":"e980-5af9-676c-4e32","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Correct completion-gate child-closure docs (superseded by 30c2ef3ad)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783053682942633001,"uuid":"ab3fcd0f-34cb-48b4-8af1-c84391d12c72"}